documents.statement: Azithromycin is sold under different trade names.
documents.explanation: The first sentence is the claim and the second sentence is the evidence. The evidence is saying "It is available as a generic medication and is sold under many trade names worldwide." The word "and" is joining two ideas together, so we can split the evidence into two parts. Part A is "It is available as a generic medication." Part B is "It is sold under many trade names worldwide." We can see that Part A is true because the medication is available as a generic. Part B is also true because it is sold under many trade names worldwide. Therefore, the entire claim is true.
documents.label: SUPPORTS
